						<summary>

						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Dundubhi (1502 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Seems to record a gift of land after purchasing it for 25 <hi rend="italic">varāha</hi> for supplying garlands, cocoanuts, betel leaves etc. to the god by <hi rend="bold">Chikka Narasaṇa-Nāyaka,</hi> on the occasion of a <hi rend="bold">lunar eclipse on the full-moon day of Kārttika in the year Dundubhi.</hi> Mentions Veṅkaṭamma. The details of date are probably equivalent to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1502, October, 15, Saturday (not Wednesday), which was a day of full-moon and lunar eclipse.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
